==Hebrew==

===Etymology===
Related to {{m|ar|丿丿||friendly, beloved}} and {{m|uga|||beloved}} (according to Even Shoshan dictionary).

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Modern Israeli}} {{IPA|he|/jadid/}}

===Noun===
{{he-noun|wv=指执|tr=yad铆d|g=m|cons=职执|pl=职执执|plcons=职执值|f=职执指|pat=拽指执}}

# A (male) platonic [[friend]].

====Usage notes====
* While the synonym {{m|he|指值专|tr=khav茅r}} is more common in Modern Hebrew, it is ambiguous between a platonic friend and a romantic one; {{m|he|指执}} may therefore be used to avoid this ambiguity, though the question {{l|he||专 专  专拽 专?|tr=khaver khaver o rak khaver?|gloss=boyfriend-friend or just friend?}} is also used.

